        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>percussion idiophones: hollow-bodied [300209185], percussion idiophones [300195371], directly struck idiophones [300041659], struck idiophones [300041657], idiophones [300041646], sound devices by acoustical characteristics [300041621], sound devices (equipment) [300387677], Sound Devices (hierarchy name) [300041619], Furnishings and Equipment (hierarchy name) [300264551], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Percussion idiophones made from the ends of oil drums, cut to a relatively shallow depth, made concave, subdivided by grooves, and hammered so as to create up to 30 segments, each of which produces a tuned pitch when struck with a rubber-headed stick.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Slaginstrumenten met maximaal 30 gestemde vlakken aangebracht op het uiteinde van ingekorte olievaten; bespeeld door erop te slaan met stokken met rubberen kop.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052452/Encyclopedie van muziekinstrumenten (1977)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>指油桶底端製成的打擊體鳴樂器，以相當淺的深度切割，製成凹形，再以溝紋細分，並以錘子敲打，製造出最多可多達三十個的不同的部份，以橡膠鼓槌敲擊，每個部份會產生一個固定的音高。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052784/TELDAP database (2009-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Schlagidiofon, hergestellt aus dem Ende eines Ölfasses, das bis zu einer relativ flachen Tiefe abgeschnitten und konkav geformt wird und in das Tonfelder getrieben werden, sodass bis zu 30 Klangflächen enstehen, von der jede eine gestimmte Tonhöhe erzeugt, wenn sie mit Gummikopfschlägeln angeschlagen wird.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
